{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:57:34.571Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Compiling & Importing Modules**\n\nI've compiled the necessary TypeScript files for the support API testing: `lib/api-auth.ts`, the core routes, and the dynamic ID routes, using `tsc`. Now, I'm importing the compiled JavaScript modules (`.js` files) into my testing script for use in the tests themselves. I'm focusing on ensuring robust test coverage, with tests for unauthorized access, etc.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:57:37.183Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing API Responses**\n\nI'm now diving into detailed response validation. My focus is the GET list and GET by ID endpoints, specifically the responses. For listing, I'll check that an Admin gets all tickets (at least three), and a Client only gets their own. Filters will be tested thoroughly for `status`, `priority`, `category`, `client_id`, `project_id`, `assigned_to`, and `search`. I'm also preparing tests for cross-tenant retrieval. For \"get by ID\", I'm checking that existing, non-existent, and unauthorized access scenarios are correctly handled. I'll be sure to check for 403 and 404 error codes.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:57:38.615Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Expanding Test Coverage**\n\nI'm now focusing on POST and PATCH operations. I'll test creating tickets with missing or invalid fields, as well as the behavior of client-created tickets with respect to client ID assignment, and admin-created tickets. For updates, I need to test PATCH for title, description, and status. I'll test client and admin update capabilities, and the restrictions to certain fields. I'm also preparing for tests that ensure only admins can assign tickets. I'm tracking down the code. I will also check the POST method for adding comments.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:57:39.843Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Clarifying Role Permissions**\n\nOkay, I'm trying to nail down the role-based access control. I'm focusing on clarifying admin/support ticket management. My primary goal is to ensure that only `gff_admin` has full access to tickets, since there's no dedicated \"support\" role in the current model. I'm reviewing the filtering logic, particularly how it interacts with the `client_id` and the `clientAssociation` to ensure that unauthorized access is blocked.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
