{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:58:22.143Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Client ID Handling**\n\nI've confirmed `getClientIdFromAssociation` functions flawlessly. Now I'm shifting focus to how `client_id` is managed within `app/api/v1/support/route.ts`, specifically the `POST` handler, and it appears this is how client roles are handled.\n\n\n**Investigating Client ID Scope**\n\nI'm now examining the \"Forbidden\" response in the `POST` handler more closely. It checks if the provided `client_id` matches the caller's associated ID, rejecting requests if they differ. I've also identified a crucial edge case: what happens when `caller.clientAssociation` doesn't map to a known `client_id`? It's mapped to \"client-unknown\" - I wonder what that signifies in terms of user roles and permitted actions. I should check `API_MOCK_USERS` for how that is handled.\n\n\n**Planning Test Cases**\n\nI'm now devising test cases for `scripts/test-support-apis.js`. I've outlined a few core scenarios. First, I'll test fetching all tickets as an admin. Then, I'll examine ticket retrieval by client, specifically for Mercer. I need to figure out what that client ID is. Next, I need to test that a user without support permissions cannot create, update, or delete tickets - I need to confirm the appropriate error responses. Finally, I'll focus on testing the client ID scoping I was observing.\n\n\n**Defining Test Retrieval Scenarios**\n\nI've specified retrieval scenarios for my tests in `scripts/test-support-apis.js`. I've determined that Mercer's ID is `client-001`, which should return two tickets, and Jenkins' ID (`client-004`) should return none. I've also detailed filtering tests by status, priority, category, and other parameters, plus searches. Furthermore, I've outlined scenarios for retrieving tickets by ID, using both admin and client roles.\n\n\n**Formulating POST Tests**\n\nI'm now detailing `POST` scenarios within `scripts/test-support-apis.js`. First, I'll confirm Mercer can create a ticket with 201 Created status, capturing the ID and verifying the `client_id` and `created_by` values. I also have to verify that Mercer can't create tickets for other clients and should receive a 403 Forbidden error. I also need to verify that admins can create tickets with 201 Created with specified `client_id`, with subsequent checks to verify the parameters match. Finally, I'll address validation scenarios for missing/invalid fields.\n\n\n**Crafting PATCH Scenarios**\n\nI'm now detailing scenarios in `scripts/test-support-apis.js` for `PATCH` requests. I need to handle updates by clients, and forbidden responses where appropriate, along with validation and role based access control (RBAC) errors. Specifically, I'm verifying the 200 OK responses, as well as several 403 Forbidden scenarios. I also have to handle invalid statuses with a 400 Bad Request.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:58:22.146Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"femjlr9b","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/scripts/test-support-apis.js","old_text":null,"new_text":"/* eslint-disable */\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\n\nconst T = path.join(__dirname, '..', 'temp-support-test-build');\nif (fs.existsSync(T)) fs.rmSync(T, { recursive: true, force: true });\n\ntry {\n  console.log(\"Compiling support APIs...\");\n  execSync('npx tsc lib/api-auth.ts app/api/v1/support/route.ts app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts app/api/v1/support/[id]/status/route.ts app/api/v1/support/[id]/assign/route.ts app/api/v1/support/[id]/comments/route.ts --outDir temp-support-test-build --module commonjs --target es2022 --moduleResolution node --esModuleInterop --skipLibCheck', { stdio: 'inherit' });\n  console.log(\"✔ Compile success.\");\n} catch (e) {\n  console.error(\"✖ Compilation failed:\", e.message);\n  process.exit(1);\n}\n\nconst apiAuth = require('../temp-support-test-build/lib/api-auth.js');\nconst supportRoute = require('../temp-support-test-build/app/api/v1/support/route.js');\nconst supportIdRoute = require('../temp-support-test-build/app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.js');\nconst statusRoute = require('../temp-support-test-build/app/api/v1/support/[id]/status/route.js');\nconst assignRoute = require('../temp-support-test-build/app/api/v1/support/[id]/assign/route.js');\nconst commentsRoute = require('../temp-support-test-build/app/api/v1/support/[id]/comments/route.js');\n\nfunction getAuth(email) {\n  const u = apiAuth.API_MOCK_USERS[email];\n  return `Bearer ${apiAuth.signJwt({ sub: u.id, email: u.email, role: u.role, name: u.name, clientAssociation: u.clientAssociation })}`;\n}\n\nasync function run() {\n  try {\n    const admin = getAuth(\"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\");\n    const clientMercer = getAuth(\"a.mercer@apex-sovereign.gff.ai\"); // client-001\n    const clientCarter = getAuth(\"e.carter@global-retail.gff.ai\"); // client-002\n    const memberJenkins = getAuth(\"s.jenkins@fed-treasury.gff.ai\"); // client-004\n    const inactiveUser = getAuth(\"m.vance@sovereign-logistics.gff.ai\"); // client-003, inactive\n\n    console.log(\"--- 1. Auth guards ---\");\n    // Inactive user should get 403\n    let res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": inactiveUser } }));\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(`Inactive user should get 403, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // No authorization header should get 401\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\"));\n    if (res.status !== 401) throw new Error(`Missing authorization header should get 401, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Invalid token should get 401\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": \"Bearer invalid\" } }));\n    if (res.status !== 401) throw new Error(`Invalid token should get 401, got ${res.status}`);\n\n\n    console.log(\"--- 2. GET Lists & Filtering ---\");\n    // Admin list should return all 3 mock tickets\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    let d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200) throw new Error(`Admin GET list status expected 200, got ${res.status}`);\n    if (!d.success || !Array.isArray(d.tickets) || d.tickets.length < 3) {\n      throw new Error(`Admin list size expected >= 3, got ${d.tickets ? d.tickets.length : null}`);\n    }\n\n    // Client Mercer (client-001) should get only their client tickets (SLA-TKT-9912, SLA-TKT-9450)\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200) throw new Error(`Client Mercer GET list status expected 200, got ${res.status}`);\n    if (d.tickets.some(t => t.client_id !== \"client-001\")) {\n      throw new Error(\"Client Mercer got tickets belonging to another client!\");\n    }\n    if (d.tickets.length !== 2) {\n      throw new Error(`Client Mercer expected 2 tickets, got ${d.tickets.length}`);\n    }\n\n    // Client Carter (client-002) should get only SLA-TKT-9801\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": clientCarter } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200) throw new Error(`Client Carter GET list status expected 200, got ${res.status}`);\n    if (d.tickets.some(t => t.client_id !== \"client-002\")) {\n      throw new Error(\"Client Carter got tickets belonging to another client!\");\n    }\n    if (d.tickets.length !== 1) {\n      throw new Error(`Client Carter expected 1 ticket, got ${d.tickets.length}`);\n    }\n\n    // Admin filter by client_id\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support?client_id=client-002\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (d.tickets.length !== 1 || d.tickets[0].id !== \"SLA-TKT-9801\") {\n      throw new Error(`Admin filtering by client_id=client-002 failed`);\n    }\n\n    // Client Mercer attempts to filter for client_id=client-002 (should return 403 Forbidden)\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support?client_id=client-002\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer } }));\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(`Client requesting cross-tenant client_id must get 403, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Filter by status=open\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support?status=open\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (d.tickets.some(t => t.status !== \"open\")) throw new Error(\"Status filtering failed\");\n\n    // Filter by priority=critical\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support?priority=critical\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (d.tickets.some(t => t.priority !== \"critical\")) throw new Error(\"Priority filtering failed\");\n\n    // Filter by category=AI Operations\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support?category=AI Operations\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (d.tickets.some(t => !t.category.includes(\"AI Operations\"))) throw new Error(\"Category filtering failed\");\n\n    // Filter by search=HSM\n    res = await supportRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support?search=HSM\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (d.tickets.length !== 1 || !d.tickets[0].title.includes(\"HSM\")) throw new Error(\"Search filtering failed\");\n\n\n    console.log(\"--- 3. GET Single Ticket by ID ---\");\n    // Admin gets SLA-TKT-9912\n    res = await supportIdRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support/SLA-TKT-9912\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: \"SLA-TKT-9912\" }) });\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200 || d.ticket.id !== \"SLA-TKT-9912\") throw new Error(\"GET single ticket as admin failed\");\n\n    // Mercer gets SLA-TKT-9912 (own)\n    res = await supportIdRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support/SLA-TKT-9912\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer } }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: \"SLA-TKT-9912\" }) });\n    if (res.status !== 200) throw new Error(`GET own ticket as client failed, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Mercer gets SLA-TKT-9801 (cross-tenant, should be 403)\n    res = await supportIdRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support/SLA-TKT-9801\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer } }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: \"SLA-TKT-9801\" }) });\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(`GET cross-tenant ticket as client must return 403, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Retrieve non-existent ticket (404)\n    res = await supportIdRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support/SLA-TKT-99999\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: \"SLA-TKT-99999\" }) });\n    if (res.status !== 404) throw new Error(`GET non-existent ticket must return 404, got ${res.status}`);\n\n\n    console.log(\"--- 4. POST Create Ticket ---\");\n    const validTicketData = {\n      title: \"Integrator Thread Overflow Error\",\n      description: \"Our integrator node is locking up on batch execution.\",\n      category: \"Infrastructure\",\n      priority: \"high\"\n    };\n\n    // Client Mercer creates ticket\n    res = await supportRoute.POST(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify(validTicketData)\n    }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 201) throw new Error(`Expected 201 on ticket creation, got ${res.status}`);\n    const createdId = d.ticket.id;\n    if (!createdId.startsWith(\"SLA-TKT-\")) throw new Error(`Invalid created ticket ID: ${createdId}`);\n    if (d.ticket.client_id !== \"client-001\") throw new Error(`Expected client_id to be Mercer's client-001, got ${d.ticket.client_id}`);\n    if (d.ticket.created_by !== \"a.mercer@apex-sovereign.gff.ai\") throw new Error(`Expected created_by to match caller, got ${d.ticket.created_by}`);\n\n    // Client Mercer attempts to pass custom client_id=\"client-002\" (should fail with 403)\n    res = await supportRoute.POST(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ ...validTicketData, client_id: \"client-002\" })\n    }));\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(`Cross-client ID injection on creation must return 403, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Admin creates ticket for client-003\n    res = await supportRoute.POST(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": admin, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        ...validTicketData,\n        title: \"Admin Created Logistics Ticket\",\n        client_id: \"client-003\"\n      })\n    }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 201) throw new Error(`Admin ticket creation expected 201, got ${res.status}`);\n    const adminCreatedId = d.ticket.id;\n    if (d.ticket.client_id !== \"client-003\") throw new Error(`Expected client_id to be client-003, got ${d.ticket.client_id}`);\n\n    // Create with validation errors:\n    // Missing title -> 400\n    res = await supportRoute.POST(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": admin, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ ...validTicketData, title: \"\" })\n    }));\n    if (res.status !== 400) throw new Error(`Missing title must return 400, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Invalid priority -> 400\n    res = await supportRoute.POST(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support\", {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": admin, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ ...validTicketData, priority: \"super-critical\" })\n    }));\n    if (res.status !== 400) throw new Error(`Invalid priority must return 400, got ${res.status}`);\n\n\n    console.log(\"--- 5. PATCH Update Ticket ---\");\n    // Client Mercer updates their own created ticket\n    res = await supportIdRoute.PATCH(new Request(`http://l/api/v1/support/${createdId}`, {\n      method: \"PATCH\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ description: \"Updated description text\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200 || d.ticket.description !== \"Updated description text\") throw new Error(\"Client PATCH own ticket failed\");\n\n    // Client Mercer attempts to update SLA-TKT-9801 (cross-tenant -> 403)\n    res = await supportIdRoute.PATCH(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support/SLA-TKT-9801\", {\n      method: \"PATCH\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ title: \"Hack attempts\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: \"SLA-TKT-9801\" }) });\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(`Client PATCH cross-tenant must get 403, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Client Mercer attempts to set assigned_to (RBAC violation -> 403)\n    res = await supportIdRoute.PATCH(new Request(`http://l/api/v1/support/${createdId}`, {\n      method: \"PATCH\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ assigned_to: \"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(`Client updating assigned_to must return 403, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Admin updates adminCreatedId with title and assignment\n    res = await supportIdRoute.PATCH(new Request(`http://l/api/v1/support/${adminCreatedId}`, {\n      method: \"PATCH\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": admin, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ title: \"Updated Logistics Ticket\", assigned_to: \"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: adminCreatedId }) });\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200 || d.ticket.title !== \"Updated Logistics Ticket\" || d.ticket.assigned_to !== \"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\") {\n      throw new Error(\"Admin PATCH update ticket failed\");\n    }\n\n\n    console.log(\"--- 6. PATCH Status Ticket ---\");\n    // Client updates own ticket status\n    res = await statusRoute.PATCH(new Request(`http://l/api/v1/support/${createdId}/status`, {\n      method: \"PATCH\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ status: \"resolved\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200 || d.ticket.status !== \"resolved\") throw new Error(\"PATCH own ticket status failed\");\n\n    // Client attempts to update cross-tenant ticket status\n    res = await statusRoute.PATCH(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support/SLA-TKT-9801/status\", {\n      method: \"PATCH\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ status: \"closed\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: \"SLA-TKT-9801\" }) });\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(`PATCH cross-tenant ticket status must return 403, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Invalid status update\n    res = await statusRoute.PATCH(new Request(`http://l/api/v1/support/${createdId}/status`, {\n      method: \"PATCH\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ status: \"invalid-status\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    if (res.status !== 400) throw new Error(`PATCH invalid status value must return 400, got ${res.status}`);\n\n\n    console.log(\"--- 7. PATCH Assign Ticket ---\");\n    // Client Mercer attempts to assign ticket -> 403\n    res = await assignRoute.PATCH(new Request(`http://l/api/v1/support/${createdId}/assign`, {\n      method: \"PATCH\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ assigned_to: \"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(`Client PATCH assign must return 403, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    // Admin assigns ticket\n    res = await assignRoute.PATCH(new Request(`http://l/api/v1/support/${createdId}/assign`, {\n      method: \"PATCH\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": admin, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ assigned_to: \"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200 || d.ticket.assigned_to !== \"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\") throw new Error(\"Admin PATCH assign failed\");\n\n\n    console.log(\"--- 8. POST Comments / Replies ---\");\n    // Client Mercer adds a comment to their own ticket\n    res = await commentsRoute.POST(new Request(`http://l/api/v1/support/${createdId}/comments`, {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ text: \"Checking if there are any updates.\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200 || !d.success || d.comment.text !== \"Checking if there are any updates.\") {\n      throw new Error(\"Client POST comment failed\");\n    }\n\n    // Admin adds a comment to Mercer's ticket\n    res = await commentsRoute.POST(new Request(`http://l/api/v1/support/${createdId}/comments`, {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": admin, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ reply: \"Our systems team has verified the thread load. It should be fully scaled now.\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200 || !d.success || d.comment.sender !== \"Dr. Sarah Vance (Admin)\") {\n      throw new Error(\"Admin POST reply failed\");\n    }\n\n    // Client Mercer attempts to post a comment to SLA-TKT-9801 (cross-tenant -> 403)\n    res = await commentsRoute.POST(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/support/SLA-TKT-9801/comments\", {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Authorization\": clientMercer, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ text: \"Can I view this?\" })\n    }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: \"SLA-TKT-9801\" }) });\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(`POST cross-tenant comment must get 403, got ${res.status}`);\n\n    console.log(\"\\x1b[32m✔ VERIFICATION SUCCESSFUL: Support Ticket CRUD APIs Fully Verified!\\x1b[0m\");\n    process.exit(0);\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(\"\\x1b[31m✖ Test failed:\\x1b[0m\", err.stack || err.message);\n    process.exit(1);\n  } finally {\n    if (fs.existsSync(T)) fs.rmSync(T, { recursive: true, force: true });\n  }\n}\n\nrun();\n","insert_line":null}}}
